WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.930 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.930 --> 00:00:08.381 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.381 --> 00:00:20.250 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.250 --> 00:00:23.280 align:middle line:10%
>> There was a Rumi saying,
"The wound is the place where

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.900 align:middle line:10%
the light enters you."

00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:27.480 align:middle line:84%
That best says what today's
guest, Sandra Ingerman,

00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:29.460 align:middle line:90%
brings to her shamanic healing.

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:31.350 align:middle line:84%
Her new book, "The
Book of Ceremony",

00:00:31.350 --> 00:00:34.140 align:middle line:84%
shares her life story and path
as a counselor, and healer,

00:00:34.140 --> 00:00:35.220 align:middle line:90%
and shaman.

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:38.220 align:middle line:84%
It's been marked by very
stark events such as three

00:00:38.220 --> 00:00:42.890 align:middle line:84%
near-death experiences, which
most people at best get one,

00:00:42.890 --> 00:00:44.730 align:middle line:90%
and you had three.

00:00:44.730 --> 00:00:46.710 align:middle line:84%
And so many of the
people that sit with me

00:00:46.710 --> 00:00:49.440 align:middle line:84%
have had near-death
experiences, usually just one,

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:52.560 align:middle line:84%
that really marked a
sweeping change in their life

00:00:52.560 --> 00:00:53.920 align:middle line:90%
in consciousness.

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:56.820 align:middle line:90%
So you required three.

00:00:56.820 --> 00:00:59.220 align:middle line:90%
And they're all so odd.

00:00:59.220 --> 00:01:01.470 align:middle line:84%
So first of all,
well, one it would

00:01:01.470 --> 00:01:03.420 align:middle line:84%
seem almost like your
little accident prone,

00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:05.160 align:middle line:84%
but, obviously,
it's more than that.

00:01:05.160 --> 00:01:07.740 align:middle line:84%
Let's start out with
you as a little kid,

00:01:07.740 --> 00:01:10.640 align:middle line:84%
because you were very
sensitive little child.

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:14.100 align:middle line:84%
And let's go into the
first time that your life

00:01:14.100 --> 00:01:17.100 align:middle line:90%
was nearly snatched away.

00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:20.610 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah, well, I grew up
in Brooklyn, New York.

00:01:20.610 --> 00:01:26.010 align:middle line:10%
And I was this
incredible nature lover,

00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:31.590 align:middle line:10%
and I loved everything
about life, and the colors.

00:01:31.590 --> 00:01:35.560 align:middle line:10%
And I thought everything
was so beautiful.

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:42.930 align:middle line:84%
And so, I was an odd child,
because I had a spiritual life

00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:45.755 align:middle line:90%
as soon as I was born.

00:01:45.755 --> 00:01:47.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Where did you get most
of your nature experience

00:01:47.880 --> 00:01:48.780 align:middle line:90%
in Brooklyn?

00:01:48.780 --> 00:01:52.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, a lot of people think
that Brooklyn has no parks

00:01:52.910 --> 00:01:53.710 align:middle line:90%
or anything.

00:01:53.710 --> 00:01:55.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, I would think it does.

00:01:55.120 --> 00:01:56.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, we had some.

00:01:56.040 --> 00:01:57.790 align:middle line:84%
>> So you went to the
parks a fair amount.

00:01:57.790 --> 00:02:00.000 align:middle line:84%
>> We went to
parks, but I also--

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:03.590 align:middle line:84%
little kids can create beauty
and magic out of everything--

00:02:03.590 --> 00:02:05.340 align:middle line:84%
>> One tree in the
neighborhood is enough.

00:02:05.340 --> 00:02:09.090 align:middle line:84%
>> And we have one tree in
front of my house that I sang

00:02:09.090 --> 00:02:10.305 align:middle line:90%
to every day.

00:02:10.305 --> 00:02:11.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, that's so sweet.

00:02:11.730 --> 00:02:14.910 align:middle line:84%
>> And would lay in the
backyard and sing to the moon,

00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:17.170 align:middle line:84%
and the moon would
sing back to me.

00:02:17.170 --> 00:02:23.400 align:middle line:84%
And so I just felt like
life was here to be enjoyed,

00:02:23.400 --> 00:02:27.150 align:middle line:84%
but yet, even at a
really, really young age,

00:02:27.150 --> 00:02:29.200 align:middle line:90%
I was aware of the suffering.

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:31.800 align:middle line:84%
I grew up in an
immigrant neighborhood,

00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:34.990 align:middle line:84%
and I just wanted to be
of some kind of help.

00:02:34.990 --> 00:02:37.410 align:middle line:84%
And so when I was
seven years old,

00:02:37.410 --> 00:02:40.750 align:middle line:84%
surprisingly, right in
my house in Brooklyn,

00:02:40.750 --> 00:02:43.620 align:middle line:84%
people always asked
how did this happen

00:02:43.620 --> 00:02:47.730 align:middle line:84%
in your house in Brooklyn,
a streak of lightning

00:02:47.730 --> 00:02:50.670 align:middle line:84%
came through the
window and hit me

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:53.242 align:middle line:90%
and threw me against the wall.

00:02:53.242 --> 00:02:54.450 align:middle line:90%
>> What are the odds of that?

00:02:54.450 --> 00:02:55.800 align:middle line:90%
>> What are the odds of that?

00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:57.330 align:middle line:90%
I mean, they're impossible.

00:02:57.330 --> 00:03:01.260 align:middle line:84%
And I went unconscious,
and I came back,

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:02.830 align:middle line:90%
and my mother was there.

00:03:02.830 --> 00:03:05.520 align:middle line:84%
And I said Mommy, I
died, Mommy, I died.

00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:07.590 align:middle line:90%
And she said, no, you didn't.

00:03:07.590 --> 00:03:10.770 align:middle line:84%
And I don't remember
any experience.

00:03:10.770 --> 00:03:13.350 align:middle line:84%
There was no spiritual
experience for me,

00:03:13.350 --> 00:03:18.300 align:middle line:84%
like later on of seeing
God and hearing the music.

00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:21.300 align:middle line:84%
But in shamanism,
shamanism being

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:26.850 align:middle line:84%
a universal, spiritual practice,
dating back over 100,000 years,

00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:31.440 align:middle line:84%
one of the signs of a shaman
is getting hit by lightning.

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:38.580 align:middle line:84%
And so at that time, I
didn't make any associations,

00:03:38.580 --> 00:03:44.730 align:middle line:84%
but as I grew, I found that
I was so hungry for anything

00:03:44.730 --> 00:03:49.170 align:middle line:84%
spiritual, anything
spiritual, and then

00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:51.570 align:middle line:84%
when I was introduced
to shamanism,

00:03:51.570 --> 00:03:53.850 align:middle line:84%
it was like oh my
god, that's it.

00:03:53.850 --> 00:03:58.680 align:middle line:84%
Being hit by lightning is
actually the sign of a shaman

00:03:58.680 --> 00:04:05.550 align:middle line:84%
and that this was my
initiation on to a life path.

00:04:05.550 --> 00:04:09.940 align:middle line:84%
>> And then the next one of
these experiences, you drown.

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:10.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:10.740 --> 00:04:12.510 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, let's talk
about that one,

00:04:12.510 --> 00:04:16.019 align:middle line:84%
because that's a great
fear of a lot of people.

00:04:16.019 --> 00:04:21.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, and that one really
opened up my life for me quite

00:04:21.420 --> 00:04:23.580 align:middle line:90%
a bit.

00:04:23.580 --> 00:04:28.230 align:middle line:84%
I lived in the '60s, and I
did the whole '60s thing.

00:04:28.230 --> 00:04:30.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, we're going to
get into that big time.

00:04:30.930 --> 00:04:33.930 align:middle line:84%
>> So during that time
was when I drowned.

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:36.780 align:middle line:84%
Some friends of mine
from the Haight Ashbury,

00:04:36.780 --> 00:04:42.840 align:middle line:84%
we went down to Mexico, and
we went swimming in the ocean

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:48.450 align:middle line:84%
in Mazatlan, and there
was a really strong tide.

00:04:48.450 --> 00:04:52.470 align:middle line:84%
And the very last things I
remember was my friend Tubby,

00:04:52.470 --> 00:04:57.750 align:middle line:84%
who was like 300 pound Mexican
bandido, yelling at me,

00:04:57.750 --> 00:05:01.500 align:middle line:84%
whatever happens,
Sandy, don't panic,

00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:06.080 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going in the water,
and I realize I can't breathe,

00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:09.850 align:middle line:84%
and I keep saying to myself,
Tubby said don't panic,

00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:11.310 align:middle line:90%
Tubby said don't panic.

00:05:11.310 --> 00:05:14.970 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
a tunnel opened up,

00:05:14.970 --> 00:05:19.000 align:middle line:84%
and I followed out into
this gorgeous light.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And I came into a stunning
landscape, a garden,

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.670 align:middle line:90%
and sat on a stone bench.

00:05:26.670 --> 00:05:30.760 align:middle line:84%
It was a territory that
doesn't exist on this planet.

00:05:30.760 --> 00:05:33.760 align:middle line:84%
And I heard the
most amazing music,

00:05:33.760 --> 00:05:37.260 align:middle line:84%
and then that was when I felt
all this pain in my chest,

00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:39.330 align:middle line:84%
and I had washed
up on the beach,

00:05:39.330 --> 00:05:42.030 align:middle line:90%
and people had brought me back.

00:05:42.030 --> 00:05:48.510 align:middle line:84%
But really, experiencing that
peace, that unconditional love,

00:05:48.510 --> 00:05:53.500 align:middle line:84%
that sound of the universe
that music of the universe,

00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:58.050 align:middle line:84%
what is holding all
of us all the time,

00:05:58.050 --> 00:06:01.140 align:middle line:84%
that set me on a path
to want to know more,

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:04.410 align:middle line:84%
and I was working at
San Francisco State,

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:06.600 align:middle line:84%
and I came back,
and my boss said,

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:09.960 align:middle line:84%
you had a near-death
experience, and so--

00:06:09.960 --> 00:06:11.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Now, why did he say that?

00:06:11.880 --> 00:06:13.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Because I told
him what happened.

00:06:13.710 --> 00:06:15.540 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, yeah.

00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:20.790 align:middle line:84%
>> And he started turning
me on to different books

00:06:20.790 --> 00:06:25.620 align:middle line:84%
on near-death experiences,
and I ended up joining Ken

00:06:25.620 --> 00:06:30.630 align:middle line:84%
Ring's organization for
near-death studies and helped

00:06:30.630 --> 00:06:34.470 align:middle line:84%
other people with near-death
experiences understand what

00:06:34.470 --> 00:06:37.380 align:middle line:90%
their experience was with them.

00:06:37.380 --> 00:06:41.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, and it wasn't over yet,
but it's jogging my own memory

00:06:41.280 --> 00:06:45.060 align:middle line:84%
of an event that happened in my
own life that I always wondered

00:06:45.060 --> 00:06:46.890 align:middle line:84%
if it was a near-death
experience because I

00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:50.190 align:middle line:84%
didn't have the grand
experience others had,

00:06:50.190 --> 00:06:51.900 align:middle line:90%
but it was drowning also.

00:06:51.900 --> 00:06:54.600 align:middle line:84%
And I just remember being
trapped under a log,

00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:57.670 align:middle line:84%
and it was slimy,
and I couldn't move.

00:06:57.670 --> 00:06:59.670 align:middle line:84%
And I'd been under, and
I thought, oh my god, I

00:06:59.670 --> 00:07:01.140 align:middle line:90%
can see the sun.

00:07:01.140 --> 00:07:03.702 align:middle line:90%


00:07:03.702 --> 00:07:05.535 align:middle line:84%
The breaking point of
the water, the surface

00:07:05.535 --> 00:07:09.360 align:middle line:84%
is only about a foot or two
away, I can see the sun.

00:07:09.360 --> 00:07:10.830 align:middle line:90%
Is this how it ends?

00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:11.630 align:middle line:90%
And that was it.

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:14.670 align:middle line:84%
Everything went black, and
my body popped up quite a bit

00:07:14.670 --> 00:07:16.380 align:middle line:90%
downstream.

00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:18.780 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know what
happened, obviously.

00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:21.660 align:middle line:84%
I passed out or something
and must have gone limp,

00:07:21.660 --> 00:07:23.760 align:middle line:84%
and it must have
allowed the stream

00:07:23.760 --> 00:07:26.160 align:middle line:84%
to take me wherever it
was going to take me.

00:07:26.160 --> 00:07:30.990 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what happened, but
I came out coughing obviously,

00:07:30.990 --> 00:07:34.480 align:middle line:84%
very shaken up, but it
was just missing time.

00:07:34.480 --> 00:07:36.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, that's the way it was--

00:07:36.100 --> 00:07:36.900 align:middle line:90%
>> The first time.

00:07:36.900 --> 00:07:37.530 align:middle line:90%
>> When I was hit by lightning.

00:07:37.530 --> 00:07:38.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:07:38.330 --> 00:07:40.680 align:middle line:84%
OK, so the story's not
over, because you also

00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:42.930 align:middle line:90%
drove off a cliff.

00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:44.700 align:middle line:90%
You were having some hard times.

00:07:44.700 --> 00:07:48.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I also have stories
that you don't have there.

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:49.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you can share them.

00:07:49.520 --> 00:07:53.730 align:middle line:84%
People love stories because we
like to see ourselves in it,

00:07:53.730 --> 00:07:56.190 align:middle line:84%
and we also like to
see what's possible,

00:07:56.190 --> 00:07:58.380 align:middle line:84%
and what's possible
to survive, you know,

00:07:58.380 --> 00:08:00.450 align:middle line:84%
the indominability
of the human spirit,

00:08:00.450 --> 00:08:02.100 align:middle line:84%
and you certainly
represent that.

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:04.560 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
the time off the cliff.

00:08:04.560 --> 00:08:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I was working
for the Forest Service,

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:15.570 align:middle line:84%
and I was up in Oregon, and
I was in a line of cars.

00:08:15.570 --> 00:08:17.700 align:middle line:90%
We were all going to work.

00:08:17.700 --> 00:08:21.150 align:middle line:84%
And some of the trucks
were going to fast

00:08:21.150 --> 00:08:25.530 align:middle line:84%
through some of the
curves, and all this dirt

00:08:25.530 --> 00:08:27.690 align:middle line:90%
came up into my windshield.

00:08:27.690 --> 00:08:31.870 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not the best
driver in the world,

00:08:31.870 --> 00:08:34.682 align:middle line:84%
and I did everything
you're not supposed to.

00:08:34.682 --> 00:08:37.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you probably panicked
and were startled by it all.

00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:39.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, and I slammed
my foot on the brakes,

00:08:39.390 --> 00:08:43.620 align:middle line:84%
and we went flying off
the cliff, five of us,

00:08:43.620 --> 00:08:46.500 align:middle line:90%
and one tree caught us.

00:08:46.500 --> 00:08:48.700 align:middle line:90%
We rolled five times.

00:08:48.700 --> 00:08:52.020 align:middle line:84%
So I got the name
Rolling Sandy after that.

00:08:52.020 --> 00:08:52.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:08:52.950 --> 00:08:56.220 align:middle line:84%
>> And we called AAA,
believe it or not.

00:08:56.220 --> 00:08:59.775 align:middle line:84%
AAA came a few hours
later and towed us out,

00:08:59.775 --> 00:09:00.900 align:middle line:90%
and we got back in the car.

00:09:00.900 --> 00:09:01.942 align:middle line:90%
>> And everyone was safe.

00:09:01.942 --> 00:09:03.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Everybody was safe.

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:06.420 align:middle line:84%
We got back in the car,
and we kept driving.

00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:13.680 align:middle line:84%
And so then, I almost got hit
by about a 10 ton boulder.

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:15.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:17.700 align:middle line:90%
>> Climbing Mount Shasta.

00:09:17.700 --> 00:09:20.370 align:middle line:90%
And that one was a big one.

00:09:20.370 --> 00:09:24.180 align:middle line:84%
I really almost died, and that
one took a long time for me

00:09:24.180 --> 00:09:27.150 align:middle line:84%
to heal from, but
the message I finally

00:09:27.150 --> 00:09:30.840 align:middle line:84%
got of what all these
near-death experiences was about

00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:36.630 align:middle line:84%
was it was time to learn that
living life on Earth was good

00:09:36.630 --> 00:09:40.260 align:middle line:84%
and to stop trying to
get out of my body.

00:09:40.260 --> 00:09:44.587 align:middle line:84%
And so Mount Shasta was
where I had that experience--

00:09:44.587 --> 00:09:45.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Tell us about it.

00:09:45.420 --> 00:09:45.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Of the boulder.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:46.980 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:09:46.980 --> 00:09:53.910 align:middle line:84%
We were climbing Mount Shasta,
and we had left base camp,

00:09:53.910 --> 00:09:57.840 align:middle line:84%
and this unbelievable
sound started

00:09:57.840 --> 00:10:00.000 align:middle line:90%
coming from the distance.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:02.430 align:middle line:84%
And I say to my friend
I'm hiking with,

00:10:02.430 --> 00:10:03.820 align:middle line:90%
do you know what's going on?

00:10:03.820 --> 00:10:07.570 align:middle line:84%
And he said, let's just
stand and wait and see.

00:10:07.570 --> 00:10:11.310 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, I see
this boulder coming at me,

00:10:11.310 --> 00:10:13.350 align:middle line:84%
and it's like it
was tracking me.

00:10:13.350 --> 00:10:15.400 align:middle line:90%
If I went right, it went right.

00:10:15.400 --> 00:10:17.810 align:middle line:90%
If I went left, it went left.

00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:22.250 align:middle line:84%
And I was wearing crampons
to help me walk in the ice.

00:10:22.250 --> 00:10:27.980 align:middle line:84%
I had to jump so hard to
get away from the boulder

00:10:27.980 --> 00:10:32.270 align:middle line:84%
that my crampon actually
got stuck up here.

00:10:32.270 --> 00:10:33.990 align:middle line:90%
That's how high I was jumping.

00:10:33.990 --> 00:10:34.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:10:34.790 --> 00:10:38.870 align:middle line:84%
>> And so my crampon
got stuck in my shirt,

00:10:38.870 --> 00:10:43.010 align:middle line:84%
and I'm hopping on one foot
while this boulder's tracking

00:10:43.010 --> 00:10:46.730 align:middle line:84%
me, and I'm going,
I have to lay down.

00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:47.780 align:middle line:90%
I have to lay down.

00:10:47.780 --> 00:10:50.580 align:middle line:90%
I can't keep jumping.

00:10:50.580 --> 00:10:55.490 align:middle line:84%
And I go, oh my god, this
is going to hurt so bad.

00:10:55.490 --> 00:10:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And I said, but
it's going to hurt

00:10:57.500 --> 00:11:00.740 align:middle line:84%
so bad for a
millionth of a second,

00:11:00.740 --> 00:11:04.760 align:middle line:84%
and I said that millionth of a
second is going to hurt so bad.

00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:06.980 align:middle line:90%
Please don't let this happen.

00:11:06.980 --> 00:11:08.240 align:middle line:90%
Please.

00:11:08.240 --> 00:11:10.170 align:middle line:90%
And it missed me by five feet.

00:11:10.170 --> 00:11:10.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:14.360 align:middle line:84%
>> And Mount Shasta is
actually my power spot.

00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:18.590 align:middle line:84%
I lived there back
in the 1970s and had

00:11:18.590 --> 00:11:22.880 align:middle line:84%
unbelievable experiences,
meeting what I believe

00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:25.020 align:middle line:90%
were the Lemurian people.

00:11:25.020 --> 00:11:29.210 align:middle line:84%
And I just had amazing
experiences hiking alone

00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:32.330 align:middle line:84%
on the mountain,
and Mount Shasta

00:11:32.330 --> 00:11:37.160 align:middle line:84%
was letting me know that I
didn't appreciate life enough,

00:11:37.160 --> 00:11:39.830 align:middle line:84%
and if I didn't
appreciate life enough,

00:11:39.830 --> 00:11:42.560 align:middle line:90%
life was going to take me out.

00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:43.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

00:11:43.520 --> 00:11:45.370 align:middle line:90%
Beyond interesting.

00:11:45.370 --> 00:11:48.050 align:middle line:84%
OK, I just came back from Mount
Shasta just a few days ago

00:11:48.050 --> 00:11:50.457 align:middle line:90%
actually, and the people--

00:11:50.457 --> 00:11:52.040 align:middle line:84%
and I was only there
for a brief time.

00:11:52.040 --> 00:11:53.457 align:middle line:84%
I've been there a
number of times,

00:11:53.457 --> 00:11:55.790 align:middle line:84%
but just for a couple days,
no big hikes or anything.

00:11:55.790 --> 00:11:57.470 align:middle line:84%
But some of the
people I was around

00:11:57.470 --> 00:12:00.380 align:middle line:84%
were talking about
these people that they

00:12:00.380 --> 00:12:04.850 align:middle line:84%
would run into there that seemed
out of place, out of time.

00:12:04.850 --> 00:12:09.320 align:middle line:84%
But they would have these kind
of interesting, intriguing,

00:12:09.320 --> 00:12:11.480 align:middle line:84%
or beautiful messages
they just kind of out

00:12:11.480 --> 00:12:14.210 align:middle line:90%
of the blue drop on someone.

00:12:14.210 --> 00:12:15.530 align:middle line:90%
So what was your experience?

00:12:15.530 --> 00:12:18.650 align:middle line:84%
When you say the Lemurians, who
did you perceive as Lemurians,

00:12:18.650 --> 00:12:20.180 align:middle line:90%
or how did they appear to you?

00:12:20.180 --> 00:12:24.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I loved hiking
in Mount Shasta by myself,

00:12:24.620 --> 00:12:27.890 align:middle line:84%
and I remember it was
a really snowy day,

00:12:27.890 --> 00:12:35.720 align:middle line:84%
and I was hiking alone, and I
sat down to just be embraced

00:12:35.720 --> 00:12:40.460 align:middle line:84%
in beauty, and I started
hearing these bells ringing,

00:12:40.460 --> 00:12:44.960 align:middle line:84%
and they were really clear bells
in the middle of the woods.

00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:48.430 align:middle line:84%
I was living there on and off,
so I was living with a friend.

00:12:48.430 --> 00:12:50.530 align:middle line:90%
So I wasn't real grounded there.

00:12:50.530 --> 00:12:54.980 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know all the stories,
the myths, the history.

00:12:54.980 --> 00:12:58.320 align:middle line:84%
And so when I got back
down to town, and I said,

00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:02.870 align:middle line:84%
well, I was out hiking, and I
heard all these amazing bells,

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:05.740 align:middle line:84%
and they said, oh,
that's the Lemurians.

00:13:05.740 --> 00:13:09.740 align:middle line:84%
They're a race of people
that live under the earth.

00:13:09.740 --> 00:13:13.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Is that in what they
termed the city of Telos,

00:13:13.550 --> 00:13:14.930 align:middle line:90%
the place called Telos?

00:13:14.930 --> 00:13:20.570 align:middle line:84%
I know that there's thought
to be a city, a place,

00:13:20.570 --> 00:13:22.940 align:middle line:84%
called Telos, where people
come and migrate back

00:13:22.940 --> 00:13:24.710 align:middle line:90%
and forth from the surface.

00:13:24.710 --> 00:13:26.660 align:middle line:84%
>> I've definitely
heard of that place,

00:13:26.660 --> 00:13:29.340 align:middle line:90%
but I hadn't heard the name.

00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:30.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

00:13:30.140 --> 00:13:33.837 align:middle line:84%
It is a fascinating place if you
can have time to actually spend

00:13:33.837 --> 00:13:34.670 align:middle line:90%
a lot of time there.

00:13:34.670 --> 00:13:37.700 align:middle line:84%
I've heard lore of all
kinds from the very lightest

00:13:37.700 --> 00:13:39.690 align:middle line:84%
to some of the
darkness there, too.

00:13:39.690 --> 00:13:40.490 align:middle line:90%
Both.

00:13:40.490 --> 00:13:44.870 align:middle line:84%
Like Sedona, it
attracts the poles,

00:13:44.870 --> 00:13:48.380 align:middle line:84%
you know, extremes, because
the energy is so potent.

00:13:48.380 --> 00:13:49.400 align:middle line:90%
>> It's so potent.

00:13:49.400 --> 00:13:51.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Whatever that
pole is is amplified.

00:13:51.800 --> 00:13:54.750 align:middle line:84%
Just stay on the light side,
I guess, is the hint there.

00:13:54.750 --> 00:13:57.680 align:middle line:84%
OK, so we'll back up
again for a moment now.

00:13:57.680 --> 00:13:59.090 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, part
of the reason you

00:13:59.090 --> 00:14:03.390 align:middle line:84%
were trying to escape your body
is because life was painful.

00:14:03.390 --> 00:14:05.690 align:middle line:84%
In your book, you said that
when you were around 13,

00:14:05.690 --> 00:14:07.610 align:middle line:84%
you really start
realizing were an empath,

00:14:07.610 --> 00:14:10.050 align:middle line:84%
and that's where your
depression was coming from

00:14:10.050 --> 00:14:12.860 align:middle line:84%
is you were actually taking
on everyone else's pain,

00:14:12.860 --> 00:14:15.620 align:middle line:84%
like you said in your
neighborhood, right?

00:14:15.620 --> 00:14:16.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:16.780 --> 00:14:18.470 align:middle line:90%
I was one of those kids.

00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:23.570 align:middle line:84%
You know, my father had a mom
and pop store a few blocks

00:14:23.570 --> 00:14:28.880 align:middle line:84%
from my house, and so I used
to go to the store after school

00:14:28.880 --> 00:14:33.120 align:middle line:84%
sometimes to help out,
and I was just-- you know,

00:14:33.120 --> 00:14:35.750 align:middle line:90%
I was only about seven or eight.

00:14:35.750 --> 00:14:37.480 align:middle line:84%
And I'd be walking
down the street

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:41.190 align:middle line:84%
and people would just stop
me and say can I talk to you,

00:14:41.190 --> 00:14:44.150 align:middle line:84%
and they'd start telling
me their problems.

00:14:44.150 --> 00:14:46.940 align:middle line:84%
And then I worked
at my father's store

00:14:46.940 --> 00:14:49.400 align:middle line:84%
from when I was like
seven, and there

00:14:49.400 --> 00:14:53.520 align:middle line:84%
was this whole group of people
who only came in to talk to me.

00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:56.630 align:middle line:84%
They would have to buy
some things, so they would.

00:14:56.630 --> 00:14:59.640 align:middle line:90%
I even remember a nun coming in.

00:14:59.640 --> 00:15:03.360 align:middle line:84%
She came in every night
that I worked, and she said,

00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:04.790 align:middle line:90%
you're such a special child.

00:15:04.790 --> 00:15:08.120 align:middle line:90%
I just come in to talk to you.

00:15:08.120 --> 00:15:14.090 align:middle line:84%
I have a capacity to listen,
and I have a capacity

00:15:14.090 --> 00:15:18.490 align:middle line:84%
to be able to really feel what
somebody is going through,

00:15:18.490 --> 00:15:22.880 align:middle line:84%
the deepest place where
they're being touched.

00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:26.720 align:middle line:84%
And I realized when
I was 13, and I

00:15:26.720 --> 00:15:30.380 align:middle line:84%
was depressed all the
time, and I was going,

00:15:30.380 --> 00:15:31.830 align:middle line:90%
I have a great life.

00:15:31.830 --> 00:15:33.390 align:middle line:90%
I love to play outside.

00:15:33.390 --> 00:15:34.280 align:middle line:90%
I love school.

00:15:34.280 --> 00:15:37.370 align:middle line:90%
Why am I so sad all the time?

00:15:37.370 --> 00:15:41.990 align:middle line:84%
And I realized I was just
picking up on so many people's

00:15:41.990 --> 00:15:48.110 align:middle line:84%
pain, and I wasn't given tools
to learn how to work with that,

00:15:48.110 --> 00:15:49.540 align:middle line:84%
you know, growing
up in a family--

00:15:49.540 --> 00:15:50.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Who is, right?

00:15:50.340 --> 00:15:54.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Where everybody's
just trying to survive.

00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:57.350 align:middle line:84%
So that became a
big part of my path

00:15:57.350 --> 00:16:00.680 align:middle line:84%
was learning how to
be there for people,

00:16:00.680 --> 00:16:04.040 align:middle line:84%
but not carry their
pain at the same time.

00:16:04.040 --> 00:16:07.190 align:middle line:84%
>> But along the way while you
were still trying to adjust

00:16:07.190 --> 00:16:11.120 align:middle line:84%
to this reality of yours, you
had what you call a functional

00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:12.160 align:middle line:90%
nervous breakdown.

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:13.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:16:13.340 --> 00:16:15.620 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:16:15.620 --> 00:16:18.510 align:middle line:84%
When the Vietnam
War came around,

00:16:18.510 --> 00:16:20.640 align:middle line:90%
it was just too much for me.

00:16:20.640 --> 00:16:24.530 align:middle line:84%
I was on Wall Street every
day, protesting, getting

00:16:24.530 --> 00:16:33.140 align:middle line:84%
hit by beer cans and gassed and
all the things that happened.

00:16:33.140 --> 00:16:37.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was only a teenager,
and I realized at that point,

00:16:37.700 --> 00:16:43.670 align:middle line:84%
I had no power to create
change, that no matter

00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:47.450 align:middle line:84%
how much I disagreed with
something politically,

00:16:47.450 --> 00:16:54.560 align:middle line:84%
I had no power to create change,
and that was the message I got.

00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:58.430 align:middle line:84%
And so what I did
at a survival--

00:16:58.430 --> 00:16:59.720 align:middle line:90%
I'm a survivalist.

00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:05.569 align:middle line:84%
I've come through a lot, and
I've come through really well.

00:17:05.569 --> 00:17:08.270 align:middle line:84%
I decided that for
my survival, it

00:17:08.270 --> 00:17:12.329 align:middle line:84%
was just best not to know what
was going on in the world.

00:17:12.329 --> 00:17:16.099 align:middle line:84%
So I stopped reading
newspapers, and I

00:17:16.099 --> 00:17:17.720 align:middle line:90%
stopped watching the news.

00:17:17.720 --> 00:17:20.810 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea who
the president was.

00:17:20.810 --> 00:17:21.890 align:middle line:90%
>> For 10 years.

00:17:21.890 --> 00:17:22.980 align:middle line:90%
>> For about 10 years.

00:17:22.980 --> 00:17:25.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Which I can't even fathom
how you could shield yourself

00:17:25.760 --> 00:17:27.829 align:middle line:84%
enough to not hear
it in passing.

00:17:27.829 --> 00:17:32.580 align:middle line:84%
So you must have led a very
solo existence during that time.

00:17:32.580 --> 00:17:35.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I had huge community.

00:17:35.790 --> 00:17:38.870 align:middle line:84%
>> How did not hear learn about
these things inadvertently?

00:17:38.870 --> 00:17:42.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we weren't
talking about politics.

00:17:42.590 --> 00:17:44.840 align:middle line:90%
>> I can understand that.

00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:47.420 align:middle line:84%
>> And I worked at
San Francisco State,

00:17:47.420 --> 00:17:51.740 align:middle line:84%
and I managed a Student
Learning Center.

00:17:51.740 --> 00:17:55.280 align:middle line:84%
And I was assistant manager
of a Student Learning Center.

00:17:55.280 --> 00:17:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
people I worked with,

00:17:57.500 --> 00:18:01.370 align:middle line:84%
he read the newspaper
every day, and so he always

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:06.710 align:middle line:84%
had that newspaper on his desk,
and so I'd just avert my eyes.

00:18:06.710 --> 00:18:10.100 align:middle line:84%
And then I got
interested, and I wanted

00:18:10.100 --> 00:18:12.260 align:middle line:90%
to look at the front page.

00:18:12.260 --> 00:18:15.830 align:middle line:84%
And I glanced down at the front
page, and for the first time,

00:18:15.830 --> 00:18:17.270 align:middle line:90%
I read the headlines.

00:18:17.270 --> 00:18:23.570 align:middle line:84%
And slowly, like a person going
through behavior training,

00:18:23.570 --> 00:18:26.730 align:middle line:84%
every day, I read another
headline and another headline

00:18:26.730 --> 00:18:27.530 align:middle line:90%
til I was--

00:18:27.530 --> 00:18:30.630 align:middle line:84%
>> To re-engage with what was
happening on the exterior.

00:18:30.630 --> 00:18:31.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:18:31.430 --> 00:18:33.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, in the
midst of all that,

00:18:33.230 --> 00:18:35.217 align:middle line:84%
and you alluded
to it a while ago,

00:18:35.217 --> 00:18:36.800 align:middle line:84%
you were living in
the Haight Ashbury.

00:18:36.800 --> 00:18:37.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:18:37.600 --> 00:18:43.040 align:middle line:84%
>> And so you were part of the
whole kind of free love or drug

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:43.840 align:middle line:90%
culture.

00:18:43.840 --> 00:18:44.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:18:44.180 --> 00:18:45.710 align:middle line:84%
>> We were there
at the same time.

00:18:45.710 --> 00:18:49.300 align:middle line:90%
I was afraid of that culture.

00:18:49.300 --> 00:18:52.040 align:middle line:84%
I just rolled in little
bumpkin from Sacramento

00:18:52.040 --> 00:18:56.870 align:middle line:84%
going to a fashion institute and
had my little fancy clothes on.

00:18:56.870 --> 00:18:59.480 align:middle line:84%
And every now and then, I'd
go through the Haight Ashbury

00:18:59.480 --> 00:19:01.070 align:middle line:84%
for some reason
or another, and I

00:19:01.070 --> 00:19:05.060 align:middle line:84%
remember being so
frightened at how disorderly

00:19:05.060 --> 00:19:08.090 align:middle line:84%
and out of control the
whole thing looked.

00:19:08.090 --> 00:19:11.270 align:middle line:84%
And also people
obviously checked

00:19:11.270 --> 00:19:14.640 align:middle line:84%
out, a lot of glassy eyes,
and like where are they?

00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:15.810 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:19:15.810 --> 00:19:18.650 align:middle line:84%
And so you were living
it to heal something

00:19:18.650 --> 00:19:22.730 align:middle line:84%
or to avoid something, the
pain or whatever inside you.

00:19:22.730 --> 00:19:24.800 align:middle line:84%
Talk about it from
that perspective.

00:19:24.800 --> 00:19:26.030 align:middle line:90%
I never got it.

00:19:26.030 --> 00:19:26.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:19:26.870 --> 00:19:30.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Because of a
natural fear of being--

00:19:30.290 --> 00:19:32.660 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, I guess
that out of control maybe.

00:19:32.660 --> 00:19:33.860 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:39.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, well, what happened for
me was being in Brooklyn during

00:19:39.110 --> 00:19:43.080 align:middle line:84%
the '60s, that was
a drug culture.

00:19:43.080 --> 00:19:47.990 align:middle line:84%
And so that was when I
got introduced to LSD

00:19:47.990 --> 00:19:51.560 align:middle line:90%
and psychedelics and marijuana.

00:19:51.560 --> 00:19:56.780 align:middle line:84%
And so I would have these
amazing spiritual experiences

00:19:56.780 --> 00:20:03.890 align:middle line:84%
of how beautiful this planet was
and that our real destiny here

00:20:03.890 --> 00:20:06.200 align:middle line:90%
was to be joyful.

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:09.470 align:middle line:84%
But I was looking around
me at all these people

00:20:09.470 --> 00:20:13.500 align:middle line:84%
who were trapped in lives
that were meaningless,

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:17.540 align:middle line:84%
and and that just brought
them to tears every day.

00:20:17.540 --> 00:20:21.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the crying I heard
growing up in Brooklyn.

00:20:21.720 --> 00:20:26.750 align:middle line:84%
And so I felt there had to
be another life somewhere.

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:31.130 align:middle line:84%
There had to be people
living a different life that

00:20:31.130 --> 00:20:33.230 align:middle line:90%
weren't so trapped.

00:20:33.230 --> 00:20:37.070 align:middle line:84%
And so I only had
stories to go by.

00:20:37.070 --> 00:20:40.310 align:middle line:84%
>> About out west, where they
said all the fruits and nuts

00:20:40.310 --> 00:20:41.110 align:middle line:90%
rolled.

00:20:41.110 --> 00:20:42.830 align:middle line:84%
I was born in San
Francisco, so I

00:20:42.830 --> 00:20:45.780 align:middle line:84%
mean it was just where I was
bathed in and was used to.

00:20:45.780 --> 00:20:46.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:20:46.580 --> 00:20:48.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, it had quite a
reputation in the rest

00:20:48.650 --> 00:20:49.450 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:20:49.450 --> 00:20:50.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah, right.

00:20:50.960 --> 00:20:55.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, I started to hear
about it, and so two of us

00:20:55.010 --> 00:21:00.830 align:middle line:84%
decided to go out there, and
the other two people got sick.

00:21:00.830 --> 00:21:03.860 align:middle line:84%
So I ended up
going out on my own

00:21:03.860 --> 00:21:08.120 align:middle line:84%
and not I mean-- my god,
talk about being ignorant.

00:21:08.120 --> 00:21:09.620 align:middle line:90%
I got an airplane.

00:21:09.620 --> 00:21:11.470 align:middle line:84%
I thought that Haight
Ashbury was going

00:21:11.470 --> 00:21:13.100 align:middle line:90%
to be right after I got off.

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:17.262 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even know how to get
anywhere or where I was going.

00:21:17.262 --> 00:21:19.220 align:middle line:84%
>> At least knew to hitch
a ride into the city.

00:21:19.220 --> 00:21:20.480 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:21:20.480 --> 00:21:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And so I met a
couple of my airplane

00:21:23.030 --> 00:21:26.510 align:middle line:84%
who took me in and
dropped me off.

00:21:26.510 --> 00:21:31.120 align:middle line:84%
I had heard about the
Good Earth commune,

00:21:31.120 --> 00:21:35.180 align:middle line:84%
and actually a movie was
made about that Stacy Keach.

00:21:35.180 --> 00:21:37.470 align:middle line:84%
So I lived there
for a few years.

00:21:37.470 --> 00:21:40.760 align:middle line:84%
And the news didn't
hit Brooklyn yet

00:21:40.760 --> 00:21:43.070 align:middle line:84%
that the Haight Ashbury
had actually been

00:21:43.070 --> 00:21:45.530 align:middle line:90%
buried in Golden Gate Park.

00:21:45.530 --> 00:21:48.630 align:middle line:84%
And so when I got there,
it was really dead.

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:49.820 align:middle line:90%
It was deserted.

00:21:49.820 --> 00:21:52.180 align:middle line:84%
There was a liquor
store on every corner,

00:21:52.180 --> 00:21:54.740 align:middle line:90%
and everything was boarded up.

00:21:54.740 --> 00:22:01.670 align:middle line:84%
But there was still enough
of this energy, this desire

00:22:01.670 --> 00:22:05.330 align:middle line:84%
of people to come together
in a different way

00:22:05.330 --> 00:22:08.840 align:middle line:84%
and to live life
from a different way,

00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:12.140 align:middle line:84%
from an expanded state
of consciousness,

00:22:12.140 --> 00:22:19.100 align:middle line:90%
from heart and love, not hate.

00:22:19.100 --> 00:22:21.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, interestingly,
even without it being Haight

00:22:21.800 --> 00:22:26.240 align:middle line:84%
Ashbury, that was more the tone
of being in California at that

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:27.053 align:middle line:90%
time.

00:22:27.053 --> 00:22:28.220 align:middle line:90%
I mean, because I was part--

00:22:28.220 --> 00:22:30.600 align:middle line:84%
I'd go see Janis
Joplin in the park,

00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:33.860 align:middle line:84%
and I was fine with all
of that, all the music.

00:22:33.860 --> 00:22:35.300 align:middle line:90%
And you know, long skirts.

00:22:35.300 --> 00:22:36.380 align:middle line:90%
Women didn't wear bras.

00:22:36.380 --> 00:22:39.500 align:middle line:84%
We didn't wear bras at
the time and organic food.

00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:43.070 align:middle line:84%
It was the drugs, but then I
didn't really even drink coffee

00:22:43.070 --> 00:22:45.830 align:middle line:90%
till I was over 40 or tea.

00:22:45.830 --> 00:22:47.540 align:middle line:90%
I just-- it didn't taste good.

00:22:47.540 --> 00:22:48.810 align:middle line:90%
None of that appealed to me.

00:22:48.810 --> 00:22:52.100 align:middle line:84%
I kind of just liked my mind as
it was, except for smoking some

00:22:52.100 --> 00:22:55.330 align:middle line:84%
ragweed in the '70s, which I'd
just bake brownies, eat, laugh,

00:22:55.330 --> 00:22:58.410 align:middle line:84%
and go to sleep, not
like what we have today,

00:22:58.410 --> 00:23:01.220 align:middle line:84%
not mind altering
in that day at all.

00:23:01.220 --> 00:23:02.660 align:middle line:84%
But it was a very
different thing

00:23:02.660 --> 00:23:07.650 align:middle line:84%
to choose to go into this deep
world of these mind altering

00:23:07.650 --> 00:23:08.450 align:middle line:90%
drugs.

00:23:08.450 --> 00:23:11.540 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I always thought, gosh,
that's really courageous on one

00:23:11.540 --> 00:23:14.542 align:middle line:84%
level, and I also thought,
that's really crazy on another

00:23:14.542 --> 00:23:17.000 align:middle line:84%
because you don't know what
it's going to do to your brain.

00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:18.620 align:middle line:90%
>> Right, exactly.

00:23:18.620 --> 00:23:23.810 align:middle line:84%
For me, I'm such
a grounded person,

00:23:23.810 --> 00:23:26.270 align:middle line:90%
I never had a bad experience.

00:23:26.270 --> 00:23:29.770 align:middle line:84%
I was really lucky I never
had a bad experience.

00:23:29.770 --> 00:23:35.150 align:middle line:84%
For me, what the draw was
and what the addiction

00:23:35.150 --> 00:23:42.500 align:middle line:84%
became for me was I would see,
no matter what drug I took,

00:23:42.500 --> 00:23:47.330 align:middle line:84%
all I saw was God, and I
experienced unconditional love.

00:23:47.330 --> 00:23:50.360 align:middle line:84%
And I was shown how we could
have a different experience

00:23:50.360 --> 00:23:52.040 align:middle line:90%
here on Earth.

00:23:52.040 --> 00:23:54.890 align:middle line:90%
And so what happened for me is--

00:23:54.890 --> 00:23:56.740 align:middle line:84%
I can't remember
what year it was.

00:23:56.740 --> 00:24:01.580 align:middle line:84%
I was probably late
20s, early 30s.

00:24:01.580 --> 00:24:06.350 align:middle line:84%
I was at a Grateful
Dead concert in Oakland,

00:24:06.350 --> 00:24:12.110 align:middle line:84%
and I was high on LSD, and
my kidneys were killing me.

00:24:12.110 --> 00:24:15.530 align:middle line:84%
And I stood there,
and I said to myself,

00:24:15.530 --> 00:24:21.590 align:middle line:84%
and I said, Sandy, so everything
is God, everything is love,

00:24:21.590 --> 00:24:25.700 align:middle line:84%
and you're hurting yourself
by taking these drugs.

00:24:25.700 --> 00:24:28.700 align:middle line:84%
Please get the message
and hang up the phone.

00:24:28.700 --> 00:24:32.180 align:middle line:84%
And so I did, and I
stopped taking drugs.

00:24:32.180 --> 00:24:35.090 align:middle line:84%
>> That's good, because you had
already got you were you were

00:24:35.090 --> 00:24:37.220 align:middle line:84%
connecting in the
most positive way.

00:24:37.220 --> 00:24:38.990 align:middle line:90%
And just as a kind of final--

00:24:38.990 --> 00:24:42.610 align:middle line:84%
I ended up probably taking
all of those over time.

00:24:42.610 --> 00:24:43.430 align:middle line:90%
A little bit of--

00:24:43.430 --> 00:24:46.740 align:middle line:84%
I mean, like once or twice,
just to see what it was.

00:24:46.740 --> 00:24:49.460 align:middle line:84%
And I'm glad I did, and
it was the same as you.

00:24:49.460 --> 00:24:51.980 align:middle line:84%
Everything was filled with
light and color and wonderful,

00:24:51.980 --> 00:24:55.900 align:middle line:84%
and one time, one dose of
ecstasy, and I was gone.

00:24:55.900 --> 00:24:58.480 align:middle line:84%
I was so out of my body, my
friend thought I was dead.

00:24:58.480 --> 00:25:00.440 align:middle line:84%
You know, I was just
having fun saying bummer,

00:25:00.440 --> 00:25:03.193 align:middle line:84%
that he's so concerned,
I'm having fun out here.

00:25:03.193 --> 00:25:04.610 align:middle line:84%
And I realized
that's probably why

00:25:04.610 --> 00:25:07.730 align:middle line:84%
I didn't do drugs is I'm
not that tethered here.

00:25:07.730 --> 00:25:10.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm not that
grounded, and it just

00:25:10.160 --> 00:25:12.272 align:middle line:90%
would not have helped things.

00:25:12.272 --> 00:25:13.730 align:middle line:84%
Where if you were
already grounded,

00:25:13.730 --> 00:25:17.070 align:middle line:84%
you needed to be lifted up to
see the beauty of what life

00:25:17.070 --> 00:25:17.870 align:middle line:90%
really is.

00:25:17.870 --> 00:25:18.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, exactly.

00:25:18.670 --> 00:25:19.952 align:middle line:90%
>> I can understand that.

00:25:19.952 --> 00:25:21.410 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for
sharing that with us.

00:25:21.410 --> 00:25:23.170 align:middle line:90%
It makes sense.

00:25:23.170 --> 00:25:26.660 align:middle line:84%
So OK, now let's get you
through to the point where

00:25:26.660 --> 00:25:29.330 align:middle line:84%
Harner, Michael
Harner, where you

00:25:29.330 --> 00:25:32.030 align:middle line:84%
met Michael Harner, and then
the real shamanistic part

00:25:32.030 --> 00:25:35.120 align:middle line:84%
of your life started
coming to fruition.

00:25:35.120 --> 00:25:37.670 align:middle line:84%
>> I went to San
Francisco State,

00:25:37.670 --> 00:25:42.830 align:middle line:84%
and I got my BA in marine
biology, and then I realized,

00:25:42.830 --> 00:25:45.380 align:middle line:84%
I really want to be
working with people.

00:25:45.380 --> 00:25:50.930 align:middle line:84%
And so I ended up in a private
graduate school, California

00:25:50.930 --> 00:25:54.770 align:middle line:84%
Institute of Asian Studies,
now California Institute

00:25:54.770 --> 00:25:57.050 align:middle line:90%
of Integral Studies.

00:25:57.050 --> 00:25:59.990 align:middle line:84%
And it was just a tiny
school in the Mission

00:25:59.990 --> 00:26:02.590 align:middle line:90%
District in San Francisco.

00:26:02.590 --> 00:26:06.260 align:middle line:84%
It was expensive, and so
I had to work two jobs

00:26:06.260 --> 00:26:09.290 align:middle line:84%
to put myself through school,
and I was always burnt

00:26:09.290 --> 00:26:12.350 align:middle line:90%
out taking 12 units a quarter.

00:26:12.350 --> 00:26:15.530 align:middle line:84%
And somebody came into the
office one day and said,

00:26:15.530 --> 00:26:17.750 align:middle line:84%
a man's coming out
from Connecticut,

00:26:17.750 --> 00:26:20.480 align:middle line:84%
I don't have a clue
what he's teaching,

00:26:20.480 --> 00:26:23.300 align:middle line:84%
